      <title>Equilibrium of Multi-Body Systems</title>
      <p>When a multipart structure is in equilibrium, each part of the structure is also in equilibrium.  For example in the truss below, each member of the truss, each joint, and each portion of the truss is also in equilibrium. This continues all the way down to the atoms of the structure. This universal equilibrium across spatial scales is one of the governing principles which allows us to break multi-body systems into smaller solvable parts. </p>
